Fairness Audit Report: UCI Adult Income Classifier
A NIST AI RMF-Structured Audit with Auditor Governance Analysis

This notebook conducts a fairness audit of a machine learning classifier trained on the UCI Adult income dataset from the AIF360 repo, using the Map, Measure, and Manage functions of the NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0) as the structural backbone. This audit computes fairness metrics on the UCI dataset, specifically focusing on the disparity of classification of "high income" between men and women, and examines a governance question: who should be responsible for conducting the audit: internal developers, external independent auditors, or a mix of both?

The audit uses Fairlearn for disaggregated metrics and threshold optimization, and AIF360 for additional metric coverage (disparate impact, statistical parity difference) and the Reweighing preprocessing mitigation.

Table of Contents
Setup- imports and dataset loading
MAP - system context, stakeholders, and audit governance
MEASURE - baseline classifier and fairness metrics
MANAGE - mitigation strategies and re-measurement
Auditor Self-Assessment - a decision tool for choosing an audit model
